title: Fire damages garage at Ōtaki Beach
text:
Two fire engines attended a garage fire at Ōtaki Beach on Wednesday night.

Fire services worked for more than three hours to extinguish a garage fire in Kāpiti.

Firefighters were called to a garage fire on Kāpiti Lane at Ōtaki Beach, at 7.14pm on Wednesday night, a fire and emergency spokesman said.

The garage was well alight when firefighters arrived. The blaze was put out by two fire engines from the Ōtaki brigade.

Firefighters were there until 11pm. A fire investigator was to attend the scene on Thursday.
